This executive order, issued on May 11, 2017, aims to strengthen the cybersecurity of federal networks and critical infrastructure in the United States. It outlines various policies and measures to be taken by executive departments and agencies to manage cybersecurity risk. It emphasizes the use of risk management processes aligned with strategic, operational, and budgetary planning. The order also promotes the use of shared IT services and the modernization of federal IT architecture. Additionally, it addresses the cybersecurity efforts of critical infrastructure entities and the need for international cooperation in cybersecurity. The order also highlights the importance of workforce development in the field of cybersecurity.